Enyioha Opara, Minna A 50 -year -old man has been arrested by the Niger State Police Command for a raping his two middle age daughters in the  Suleja Local Government Area of the state. The suspect, Peter Ayemoba,  was picked up by the police after a complaint by a relation of his family. Ayemoba was alleged to have started having the canal knowledge of his two daughters for over six years. It was gathered that the victims are between the ages of 20 and 22 and had been having sex with their father since 2013 until he found himself in police net. It was said that the suspect had on several occasions threaten to kill the women and commit suicide if they deny him sex. Ayemoba said, “The last thing my daughters will do is to deny me sex when I want it especially when I am drunk, once the spirit of having sex befalls me  any of them that is available will have sex with me.” The Police Public Relations Officer, Wasiu Abiodun, confirmed the incident,  saying the suspect confessed to the crime. Copyright PUNCH.
